'''误差棒'''，又称为'''误差线'''（{{lang-en|error bar}}），是一种在[[统计图表|统计图表]]中表示[[误差|误差]]的线段<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sarkar|first=Advait|last2=Blackwell|first2=Alan F.|last3=Jamnik|first3=Mateja|last4=Spott|first4=Martin|url=https://advait.org/files/sarkar_2015_uncertainty_vis.pdf|doi=10.2312/eurovisshort.20151138|year=2015|journal=Eurographics Conference on Visualization (Eurovis) - Short Papers|title=Interaction with Uncertainty in Visualisations|access-date=2021-03-14|archive-date=2020-09-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200926231558/https://advait.org/files/sarkar_2015_uncertainty_vis.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。误差棒越长，代表该项数据误差越大，反之亦然。误差棒的长度一般等同于该项数据的[[标准差|标准差]]或[[标准误|标准误]]。

一个对误差棒的常见误解是两项数据之间误差棒互不覆盖同一区间即代表这两项数据之间存在[[显著性差异|显著的统计学差异]]。但其实不然。两项数据的误差线是否覆盖同一区间不能用作判断两项数据之间是否存在显著性差异的方法<ref name="Error bars in experimental biology">{{cite journal|last1=Cumming|first1=Geoff|last2=Fidler|first2=Fiona|last3=Vaux|first3=David L.|title=Error bars in experimental biology|journal=The Journal of Cell Biology|date=9 April 2007|volume=177|issue=1|pages=7–11|doi=10.1083/jcb.200611141|pmid=17420288|pmc=2064100}}</ref><ref name="The (mis)use of overlap of confidence intervals to assess effect modification">{{cite journal|last1=Knol|first1=Mirjam J.|last2=Pestman|first2=Wiebe R.|last3=Grobbee|first3=Diederick E.|title=The (mis)use of overlap of confidence intervals to assess effect modification|journal=European Journal of Epidemiology|date=19 March 2011|volume=26|issue=4|pages=253–254|doi=10.1007/s10654-011-9563-8|pmid=21424218|pmc=3088813}}</ref><ref name="Munger">{{cite web|last1=Munger|first1=Dave|title=Most researchers don't understand error bars|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101122420/http://scienceblogs.com/cognitivedaily/2008/07/31/most-researchers-dont-understa-1/|website=Cognitive Daily|access-date=17 March 2018}}</ref><ref name="Researchers misunderstand confidence intervals and standard error bars">{{cite journal|last1=Belia|first1=Sarah|last2=Fidler|first2=Fiona|last3=Williams|first3=Jennifer|last4=Cumming|first4=Geoff|title=Researchers misunderstand confidence intervals and standard error bars|journal=Psychological Methods|date=2005|volume=10|issue=4|pages=389–396|doi=10.1037/1082-989X.10.4.389|pmid=16392994}}</ref>。

